text:
="preserve">David Tyre Bishop (March 9, 1929 – August 3, 2020) was an American lawyer and politician. Bishop was born in Syracuse, New York. He was a member of the Minnesota House of Representatives from 1983 to 1992 and 1993 to 2002. He was a Republican.
Bishop died on August 3, 2020 in Rochester, Minnesota at the age of 91.
